{"lemma":"مُخَنَّثٌ","slug":"مُخَنَّثٌ","root":"خ.ن.ث","root_slug":"خ-ن-ث","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ن-ث","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11582"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AE%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%AB%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"effeminate one or male who resembles a woman","tags":["Arabic","Standard","derogatory","often"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of خَنَّثَ (ḵannaṯa)","tags":["form-of","participle","passive"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"effeminate","tags":["derogatory","often"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"hermaphrodite (“having both male and female parts or functions”)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of the verb خَنَّثَ (ḵannaṯa, “to bend, to make effeminate”)."},"ipa":["/mu.xan.naθ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11582","headword_ar":"مُخَنَّثٌ","root":"xnv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xan~ava","text_ar":"خَنَّثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“he bent,” (S, K,) because of his softness, delicacy, tenderness, flabbiness, laxness, or limberness, and affectation of languor, or languidness; (TA;) or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xunovaY","text_ar":"خُنْثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Kh, JK, MS;) An"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effeminate"},{"kind":"text","text":"man; (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anv","text_ar":"انث"},{"kind":"text","text":", and TA;) one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who resembles a woman in gentleness, and in softness of speech, and in an affectation of languor of the limbs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^an~avN","text_ar":"مُوَنَّثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanivN","text_ar":"خَنِثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) it is written thus and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxan~ivN","text_ar":"مُخَنِّثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) this latter is explained by some as meaning one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who makes his speech like that of women, in softness and gentleness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) it is also said that both these epithets are used to signify one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who affects languor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languidness, of the limbs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who makes himself like women in the bending of himself, and in affecting languor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languidness, and in speech:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but that one uses the latter epithet only when he means one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does what is excessively foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscene;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a catamite;"},{"kind":"text","text":"though this is a meaning often borne by the former also;] notwithstanding that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxoniyvN","text_ar":"تَخْنِيثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as signifying the “committing such an action,” was unknown to the Arabs [of the classical ages], and is not found in their language: (MF, TA:) [often, also,] the former epithet signifies a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incapable of venery:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA:) it is said in a trad. that they used to reckon the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mxn~v","text_ar":"مخنّث"},{"kind":"text","text":"as one of those having no need of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nikaAH","text_ar":"نِكَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arb","text_ar":"ارب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxan~av","text_ar":"مُخَنَّث"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xunaAvapu","text_ar":"خُنَاثَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xunayovapu","text_ar":"خُنَيْثَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[each imperfectly decl.]. (K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Msb","MF","MA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}